## Fluxo de Dados: Criação de Tarefa

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor U as Usuário
    participant F as Frontend (Alpine)
    participant C as TaskController
    participant V as CreateTaskRequest
    participant A as CreateTask Action
    participant M as Task Model
    participant O as TaskObserver
    participant DB as Database

    U->>F: Preenche formulário
    F->>C: POST /api/tasks
    C->>V: validate()
    V-->>C: OK (or 422)
    C->>A: execute(validated)
    A->>M: Task::create()
    M->>DB: INSERT tasks
    DB-->>M: task created
    M-->>A: $task
    A-->>C: $task
    C->>O: created($task)
    O->>DB: INSERT task_history (initial state)
    C-->>F: 201 JSON {task}
    F-->>U: Atualiza UI
```

---

## Fluxo de Dados: Kanban Drag-and-Drop

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor U as Usuário
    participant K as Kanban (Alpine + Sortable)
    participant A as API /tasks/{id}/status
    participant C as TaskController
    participant M as Task Model
    participant O as TaskObserver
    participant H as TaskHistory

    U->>K: Arrasta card para "Concluído"
    K->>K: @dragend = novoStatus
    K->>A: PATCH /tasks/{id}/status {status: done}
    A->>C: __invoke(request, task)
    C->>M: task->update(['status' => 'done'])
    M->>O: updated(task)
    O->>H: TaskHistory::create(from, to, user_id)
    C-->>K: 200 JSON {task}
    K->>K: Atualiza card localmente
```

